From: Stefan Metzmacher <metze@samba.org>
Date: Wed, 14 Sep 2022 05:25:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] cifs: don't send down the destination address to sendmsg for
 a SOCK_STREAM
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.19.11
Git-commit: 17d3df38dc5f4cec9b0ac6eb79c1859b6e2693a4

commit 17d3df38dc5f4cec9b0ac6eb79c1859b6e2693a4 upstream.

This is ignored anyway by the tcp layer.

Signed-off-by: Stefan Metzmacher <metze@samba.org>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Reviewed-by: Ronnie Sahlberg <lsahlber@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Paulo Alcantara (SUSE) <pc@cjr.nz>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/cifs/transport.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/cifs/transport.c b/fs/cifs/transport.c
index bfc9bd55870a..2281743ea1c4 100644
--- a/fs/cifs/transport.c
+++ b/fs/cifs/transport.c
@@ -196,8 +196,8 @@ smb_send_kvec(struct TCP_Server_Info *server, struct msghdr *smb_msg,
 
 	*sent = 0;
 
-	smb_msg->msg_name = (struct sockaddr *) &server->dstaddr;
-	smb_msg->msg_namelen = sizeof(struct sockaddr);
+	smb_msg->msg_name = NULL;
+	smb_msg->msg_namelen = 0;
 	smb_msg->msg_control = NULL;
 	smb_msg->msg_controllen = 0;
 	if (server->noblocksnd)
